{:proof/problem-id "apm-a96J03", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (integrable \\(f\\), Lebesgue measure, translations, the \\(L^1\\) norm) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target only asserts \\(\\|f(\\cdot-t)-f\\|_{L^1}\\!\\to 0\\) after assuming \\(f\\in L^1\\)) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (translation continuity in \\(L^1\\) is a standard standalone theorem) · notes: the helper lemma isolates the dense subclass (compactly supported continuous functions) where uniform continuity gives the limit directly.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Prove translation continuity in L¹: ‖f(·-t)-f‖₁ → 0 as t→0.\"\n :terms [{:name \"density of nice functions\"\n          :meaning \"Smooth compactly-supported or simple functions are dense in L¹(ℝ).\"\n          :needed-because \"Approximate f by a function whose translates are easily controlled.\"}\n         {:name \"uniform continuity on compact support\"\n          :meaning \"A continuous compactly-supported g satisfies sup_{|t|<η}|g(x-t)-g(x)|→0.\"\n          :needed-because \"Gives the L¹ control for the approximant g.\"}\n         {:name \"triangle inequality split\"\n          :meaning \"‖f(·-t)-f‖₁ ≤ ‖f-g‖₁ + ‖g(·-t)-g‖₁ + ‖g-f‖₁.\"\n          :needed-because \"Combines approximation and uniform continuity.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Density of C_c(ℝ) in L¹\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 approximation\"\n             :why-this-now \"Choose g with ‖f-g‖₁ < ε/3 so that the error term is small.\"\n             :lean-target \"l1_dense_in_compacts\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has density of simple/SW functions; likely already available.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"Uniform continuity of compactly-supported g\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 triangle inequality\"\n             :why-this-now \"Show ‖g(·-t)-g‖₁ < ε/3 for |t| small by bounding integration over compact support.\"\n             :lean-target \"translation_continuity_compact\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Need lemma about L¹ norm continuity for C_c functions; should follow from dominated convergence.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"For every f ∈ L¹(ℝ), the translations converge in L¹: ‖f(·-t)-f‖₁ → 0 as t→0.\"\n             :formal-name \"translation_continuity_L1\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ f : ℝ → ℝ, Integrable f volume → Tendsto (fun t => ∫⁻ x, |f (x - t) - f x| ∂volume) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0)\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Exact statement of translation continuity in L¹.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"translation_continuity_L1\"\n              :formal-statement \"∀ f : ℝ → ℝ, Integrable f volume → Tendsto (fun t => ∫⁻ x, |f (x - t) - f x| ∂volume) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0)\"\n              :informal-clause \"Main theorem.\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"translation_continuity_compact\"\n              :formal-statement \"∀ g ∈ C_c(ℝ), Tendsto ‖g(·-t)-g‖₁ (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0)\"\n              :informal-clause \"Handles the dense subclass before approximation.\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Why it’s hard.** The integrand \\(|f(x-t)-f(x)|\\) involves two samples of \\(f\\) at different points, so you can’t apply dominated convergence with a single dominator right away. The trap is trying to bound it directly by an \\(L^1\\) function. Instead, approximate \\(f\\) by a “nice” function whose translates are controllable.\n\n**Key insight.** Approximate \\(f\\) in \\(L^1\\) by a continuous, compactly supported \\(g\\). Uniform continuity of \\(g\\) on its compact support makes \\(|g(x-t)-g(x)|\\) small uniformly in \\(x\\) for small \\(t\\), so the \\(L^1\\)-norm of \\(g(\\cdot-t)-g\\) goes to zero. Then\n\\[\n\\|f(\\cdot-t)-f\\|_{1} \\le \\|f-g\\|_{1} + \\|g(\\cdot-t)-g\\|_{1} + \\|g-f\\|_{1},\n\\]\nand each term can be forced below \\(\\varepsilon/3\\).\n\n**Complete proof.** Let \\(\\varepsilon>0\\). Pick \\(g\\in C_c(\\mathbb R)\\) with \\(\\|f-g\\|_{1}<\\varepsilon/3\\) (density of \\(C_c\\) in \\(L^1\\)). Then, for some compact \\(K\\), \\(g\\) vanishes outside \\(K\\) and is uniformly continuous there, so \\(|g(x-t)-g(x)|\\le \\eta\\) for all \\(x\\) when \\(|t|<\\delta\\). Since \\(|g(x-t)-g(x)|\\le 2\\|g\\|_\\infty\\) and vanishes off a fixed compact set, the dominated convergence theorem gives \\(\\int |g(x-t)-g(x)|<\\varepsilon/3\\) for \\(|t|<\\delta\\). Thus\n\\[\n\\int |f(x-t)-f(x)| \\le \\|f-g\\|_1 + \\|g(\\cdot-t)-g\\|_1 + \\|g-f\\|_1 < \\varepsilon\n\\]\nwhenever \\(|t|<\\delta\\), proving \\(\\|f(\\cdot-t)-f\\|_1 \\to 0\\).\n\n**Lean 4 formalization.**\n- Main target (`formal-alignment.edn`):\n  ```lean\n  theorem translation_continuity_L1\n      (hf : Integrable f volume) :\n      Tendsto (fun t => ∫⁻ x, |f (x - t) - f x| ∂volume) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0)\n  ```\n- Helper (`translation_continuity_compact`): handle \\(g\\in C_c(\\mathbb R)\\) via uniform continuity and `tendsto_integral_of_dominated_convergence`.\n- Plan (`proof-plan.edn`): approximate \\(f\\) by \\(g\\), control the compact case, and combine via the triangle inequality. Stage 3 is still “in progress”—these lemmas need to be coded in `Main.lean`, but Mathlib already supplies the density and dominated-convergence machinery.\n\n**What connects.** Translation continuity underlies convolution approximation, Fourier analysis, and mollifier constructions. The “dense subclass + triangle inequality” trick is standard: prove the claim on \\(C_c\\), then boot-strap to general \\(L^1\\).\n\n_All artifacts (execute/proof-plan/formal-alignment/changelog) are populated in `/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/` with Stage 3 marked in progress._", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J03/Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538", :frame/id "apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T00:27:41.568013Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A96J03.Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538", :proof/problem-id "a96J03", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J03/apm-v2-a96J03-1775003261538/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J03/Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J03/Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538/Scratch.lean"}}, :proof/artifacts ["/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J03/Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538/Main.lean" "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J03/Apm_v2_a96J03_1775003261538/Scratch.lean"], :proof/elapsed-ms 59915}